bodyClass: home
---

<header class="hero">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="wordmark-hero">
            <span class="syn">syn</span><span class="l">l</span><span class="y">y</span><span class="n">n</span><span class="k">k</span>
        </div>
        <p class="tagline">The harness that turns AI tools into a team.</p>
        <p class="description">
            A single-file Python CLI that injects project context, dispatches agents, tracks capability, and runs an always-on HTTP context server — so your agents share state instead of starting from scratch.
        </p>

        <div class="code-block-wrapper">
            <div class="code-block">
                curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nikhilsoman/synlynk/main/install.sh | bash
            </div>
            <button class="copy-btn" data-copy="curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nikhilsoman/synlynk/main/install.sh | bash" title="Copy to clipboard">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M16 1H4c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14h2V3h12V1zm3 4H8c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h11c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V7c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 16H8V7h11v14z"/></svg>
            </button>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-ctas">
            <a href="#install" class="btn primary">Get started →</a>
            <a href="{{ site.github_url }}" class="btn outline">View on GitHub</a>
        </div>

        <div class="requirement-badges">
            <span class="badge">v{{ site.version }}</span>
            <span class="badge">Python 3.8+</span>
            <span class="badge">stdlib only</span>
            <span class="badge">MIT</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</header>

<section class="problem">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label">The Problem</div>
        <blockquote>
            Every AI session starts from scratch. Agents don't know what the last agent decided, can't see what's running, and have no shared memory. The more agents you add, the worse the coordination gets.
        </blockquote>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="how-it-works" class="how-it-works">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label">How it works</div>
        <div class="step-grid">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <h3>init</h3>
                <p>Bootstrap <code>project-docs/</code> and AI instruction files — one setup, every agent reads the same state</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <h3>exec</h3>
                <p>Wrap any AI CLI — synlynk injects context, captures tokens, enforces budgets, detects failure loops</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <h3>dispatch</h3>
                <p>Queue work for Claude, Codex, or Agy — synlynk routes to the best-fit agent based on capability scores</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">4</div>
                <h3>daemon</h3>
                <p>Always-on process keeps <code>context.md</code> fresh and exposes it over HTTP so agents pull without invoking the CLI</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="features">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label">Features</div>
        <div class="feature-grid">
            <div class="feature-card">
                <span class="glyph">⟡</span>
                <h3>Context injection</h3>
                <p>Reads <code>project-docs/</code> into <code>context.md</code> before every exec — every AI session starts with current project state, no setup required</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <span class="glyph">◉</span>
                <h3>Always-on daemon</h3>
                <p>New in v0.9.3 — <code>synlynk daemon start</code> runs a background process with an HTTP API on <code>localhost:27471</code>; agents pull context over HTTP and dispatch jobs without invoking the CLI</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <span class="glyph">◳</span>
                <h3>Persistent job queue</h3>
                <p>Priority-ordered <code>daemon_jobs</code> in SQLite with dependency chains — jobs survive daemon restarts; crashed dispatches never produce duplicate runs</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <span class="glyph">◈</span>
                <h3>Capability engine</h3>
                <p>Every dispatch scores the agent's performance across 40+ domains — quality, speed, cost, test results. Routing improves as data accumulates. Ratings are Ed25519-signed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <span class="glyph">⬡</span>
                <h3>Team coordination</h3>
                <p><code>synlynk join</code>, <code>synlynk team status</code>, <code>synlynk decide</code> — multi-agent consensus panels, pull-before-write arbitration, and team digests across all contributors</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <span class="glyph">◬</span>
                <h3>Sentinel &amp; cost controls</h3>
                <p>Flatline detection halts after 3 consecutive identical failures. Budget limits with 80% warnings. Per-session token tracking across every agent.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="install-band" id="install">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label">Install</div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; font-size: 14px;">Installs to <code>~/.synlynk/bin/synlynk</code> — no dependencies beyond Python 3.8+</p>
        <div class="code-block-wrapper">
            <div class="code-block">
                curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nikhilsoman/synlynk/main/install.sh | bash
            </div>
            <button class="copy-btn" data-copy="curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nikhilsoman/synlynk/main/install.sh | bash">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M16 1H4c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14h2V3h12V1zm3 4H8c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h11c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V7c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 16H8V7h11v14z"/></svg>
            </button>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 1rem; display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <div class="code-block-wrapper secondary" style="flex: 1; min-width: 240px;">
                <div class="code-block">synlynk init</div>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block-wrapper secondary" style="flex: 1; min-width: 240px;">
                <div class="code-block">synlynk daemon start</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="roadmap">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label">Roadmap</div>
        <div class="roadmap-grid">
            <div class="roadmap-item shipped">
                <div class="status-dot"></div>
                <h3>v0.9.3 — shipped</h3>
                <p>Async Daemon: <code>synlynk daemon</code>, persistent job queue, 10-endpoint HTTP API on <code>localhost:27471</code>, launchd/systemd/crontab service install. 432 tests.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="roadmap-item shipped">
                <div class="status-dot"></div>
                <h3>v0.9.x — shipped</h3>
                <p>Kernel fixes, install hardening, team onboarding (<code>synlynk join</code>), multi-agent consensus (<code>synlynk decide</code>), Ed25519 capability signing, source architecture scanning.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="roadmap-item active">
                <div class="status-dot"></div>
                <h3>v0.9.4 — next</h3>
                <p>Workgroup Relay: WSS/443 relay, 3 deployment modes (LAN / Cloudflare Tunnel / VPS), revolving host protocol — so agents on different machines share context without a shared filesystem.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="roadmap-item">
                <div class="status-dot"></div>
                <h3>v1.0 — the OS</h3>
                <p>Stable API, pipx/Homebrew packaging, open context protocol, signed capability ledger, Tokq cloud bridge, synlynk.com community server.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="roadmap-cta">
            <a href="{{ site.github_url }}/discussions">Vote on what to build next →</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
